{"sequence":40,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T17:54:03.896025537Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-de3fa6ce","body":"finding_summary: Active milestone persistence is missing from the milestone-scoped project creation paths, so the new omitted-ID behavior still breaks after normal workflows. In `src/cli/project.rs:267-292`, the `RequirementsCreateHandoff::MilestoneBundle` branch materializes and prints a milestone but never records it as the active milestone. In `src/cli/project.rs:303-529`, `project create-from-bead` / `task create` creates a project for an explicit `milestone_id` but also never updates the active milestone. Because `milestone next/run` resolve omitted IDs only from the `active-milestone` pointer (`src/cli/milestone.rs:470-489`), running either creation flow and then invoking `ralph-burning milestone next` or `ralph-burning milestone run` without an explicit ID will still use stale state or fail with `NoActiveMilestone`.\nseverity: medium\naffected_files:\n- src/cli/project.rs\n- src/cli/milestone.rs\nremediation_hint: Move active-milestone persistence into a shared helper and call it after successful milestone materialization / bead-backed project creation, then add CLI coverage for those flows followed by `milestone next/run` without an ID.","dedup_key":"30447b2d3e30ecd671101c069aafe890176594947f989e45cf319e36c8c92740","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415164250","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":41,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T17:54:03.907311444Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-db2d60b4","body":"canonicalize_milestone_bead_ref and its caller (milestone_bead_refs_match / milestone_bead_ids_equivalent) are copy-pasted identically into src/cli/milestone.rs:1023-1036, src/cli/project.rs:971-984, and src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:1398-1410. Likewise br_show_output_indicates_missing (milestone.rs:1038) and br_show_exit_looks_missing (project.rs:986) are identical except for name. Extract these into a shared module or onto the MilestoneId type to prevent silent divergence. This is bead identity resolution logic — if one copy evolves without the others, the controller, CLI next/run, and project create codepaths will disagree on which bead belongs to which milestone.","dedup_key":"8c5adf55e4590b27242ba8691784e6656dc4e0e34d58cd17e48634c9c292fcc5","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6-max","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260415164250","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":42,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T17:54:03.916778844Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-613a6cff","body":"br_show_output_indicates_missing (milestone.rs:1038) and br_show_exit_looks_missing (project.rs:986) use message.contains(\"not found\") && message.contains(\"issue\") as the effective check (the first disjunct is a strict subset of the second and adds no filtering). The word \"issue\" is overloaded — it means both tracker-issue and error-problem. An error like \"permission issue: path not found\" would match, causing load_bead_detail_from_br to return Ok(None), which propagates to ControllerBeadStatus::Missing at milestone.rs:1108, treated as Closed by the controller at controller.rs:941 — silently skipping an open bead. Fix: drop the loose second disjunct and keep only the specific substring checks (\"bead not found\", \"issue not found\"), or use a more precise pattern.","dedup_key":"9e0a8f9a114cad83f260507db60a11c11361351335656d9d39ef955957cd8d99","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6-max","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260415164250","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
