{"sequence":61,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T18:27:04.786717075Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-78e7fc68","body":"finding_summary: `ProjectMilestoneControllerRuntime::bead_status` still trusts the first element returned by `br show <short-id> --json` when `br` returns multiple matches (`src/cli/run.rs:930-957`). This is reachable because the controller deliberately preserves raw short refs from `br ready`, so a later `run start`/`run resume` can query `br show bead-1` for a milestone-owned bead. If another milestone also has `bead-1`, the runtime can read the foreign bead's status and incorrectly move the controller to `needs_operator`/`reconciling` or block execution for the wrong reason.\nseverity: medium\naffected_files:\n- src/cli/run.rs:930-957\nremediation_hint: Handle `BrShowResponse::Many` the same way `request_bead_detail` and the new milestone CLI loaders do: filter candidates with `milestone_bead_refs_match(...)`, reject ambiguous multi-matches, and only then derive `ControllerBeadStatus`.","dedup_key":"6127b00a16ad037798f88e906f28cac9093b60a25626269d54edf4898bf8f5e4","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415164250","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":62,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T18:27:04.796067830Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-8da55614","body":"finding_summary: Omitted `milestone_id` still resolves from a single persisted `active-milestone` file (`src/cli/milestone.rs:487-495`), but several commands that clearly switch the user's milestone context never refresh that state. `project select` only updates the active project (`src/cli/project.rs:161-166`), and `run start`/`run resume` load bead-backed project metadata without updating the active milestone (`src/cli/run.rs:3370-3376`, `src/cli/run.rs:3543-3548`). After switching to a project from milestone B, `milestone next`/`milestone run` without an explicit ID can still operate on stale milestone A, or fail with `NoActiveMilestone` in workspaces that only have an active bead-backed project.\nseverity: medium\naffected_files:\n- src/cli/milestone.rs:487-495\n- src/cli/project.rs:161-166\n- src/cli/run.rs:3370-3376\n- src/cli/run.rs:3543-3548\nremediation_hint: Either update `active-milestone` whenever the active project changes to a bead-backed project, or make `resolve_active_milestone` fall back to the active project's `task_source.milestone_id` before returning `NoActiveMilestone`.","dedup_key":"036cee8057763b394f397f7fc8cfb0916bbc49845bcacace234b2abf7ae12470","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415164250","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
